					<head>Esther scroll</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79053644" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Book of Esther. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="la"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="1r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Megilat Ester </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מגלת אסתר</title>
							<note>
								<p>Some readings differ from the masoretic כתיב. </p>
								<p>The first six columns (written in different hand than the rest of the scroll) are provided with vowel-points, and accompanied by an interlinear Latin translation. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment scroll of the 15th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment. </support>
								<extent>7 membranes, 24 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>440/600</height>
										<width>4700</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>7 membranes, with wooden roller and modern wrapper. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>One end of wooden roller missing.
</p>
									<p>Long edges dark from damp. </p>
									<p>Spills occasionally continue across text area. </p>
									<p>General usage stains, creases, very occasional worming.
</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="24" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible pricking. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on עטנזגץ, six on ש, and one on the letter ח. </p>
									<p>The names of the sons of Haman arranged in 6 lines. </p>
									<p>Few occurances of majuscular and minuscular letters. </p>
									<p>Sections 1:7, 2:21, 3:1, 8:3, 9:29 are open. </p>
									<p>Wooden roller (600mm high). </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
